#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""jump — the one-command interface to the Jump Height device.

Your job is hardware (wires, glue, water). This tool does everything else.

    ./tools/jump setup       one-time: install the toolchain
    ./tools/jump simtest     full software test suite, no hardware needed
    ./tools/jump flash       build + upload firmware, then self-test the device
    ./tools/jump selftest    check wiring/sensor/storage, plain-English hints
    ./tools/jump desktest    guided assembly check (3 tosses onto a cushion)
    ./tools/jump drop        guided calibration from measured drops
    ./tools/jump sync        download a session, analyze it, write a report
    ./tools/jump replay      re-run the detector over a saved capture CSV
    ./tools/jump monitor     raw serial console
    ./tools/jump gen         regenerate firmware params from config/params.json

desktest / drop / selftest / sync accept --fake to run against a simulated
device (tools/fake_device.py) — rehearse the whole flow with zero hardware.

Requires Python 3.8+. Serial I/O uses pyserial if installed, else a built-in
POSIX fallback (Linux/macOS). Windows users: `setup` installs pyserial.
"""

